Installation Instructions
*************************


The scripts and the module use the Python-setuptools packaging systems.
Just be sure than Python & Setuptools package is installed on your computer

Steeps :
1) create the directory where the saves will be keeps if they did not exists :
| su mkdir /home/base/sauve_jours
| su mkdir /home/base/sauve_semaines
| su mkdir /home/base/sauve_mois
2) Unpack the distribution somewhere like /usr/local/src
| tar zxvf sauve_bases-x.x.tar.gz
3) Enter into this directory and just type :
| su python setup.py install

Normaly thats all !


The setup script have :
- Create a module for the scripts under /sur/local/lib/python2.x/site-packages/sauve_bases.py 
(or under /usr/local/lib64 if you have a x64 machine)
- Create databases save scripts under /usr/local/bin :
/usr/local/bin/sauve_jour.sh
/usr/local/bin/sauve_semaine.sh
/usr/local/bin/sauve_mois.sh
- Create symbolics for cron usage :

